Here, Psp and Ppz are the spontaneous and piezoelectric polarizations. It should be noted that the induced-polarization at the InGaN/GaN hetero-interface depends on the indium content in the InGaN epilayer and can be calculated using an ab initio model developed by Fiorentini et al. [11, 16]. Definitely, due to charge spreading at the vicinity of the interface, the polarization charges are distributed in a few atomic layers as thick as 1 nm [11, 12], called Wpz. Hereafter; we assume that the polarization charges can be described by a bulk charge density ρpz such as:3ρpz=PWpz.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
