The short-circuit current given in a PV module datasheet is for standard test conditions of irradiance and air mass at a temperature of 25 °C, G0 = 1000 W/m2, for AM1.5. Accordingly, for any given irradiance G, the PV cell current can be adjusted using the following law [19]:13Isc/G=GG0Isc/G0.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
